    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-11-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-11-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="247"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d247">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Malmros</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Colon</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-11-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 3, 1903</hi>.</date>(Received 2.35
                        p.m.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Revolution imminent. Government force on the Isthmus about 500 men. Their
                    officers promised support revolution. Fire department Panama, 441, are well
                    organized and favor revolution. Government vessel, <hi rend="italic"
                        >Cartagena</hi>, with about 400 men, arrived early to-day with new commander
                    in chief, Tobar. Was not expected until November 10. Tobar’s arrival is not
                    probable to stop revolution.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Malmros</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
